<subSubSection id="C3556543FFB6FFACFF59FE99FF7CFE64" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF036C8FFB6FFACFF59FE99FF7CFE64" blockId="7.[151,1436,152,448]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="B93BEADAFFB6FFACFF59FE99FED6FED6" bold="true" box="[198,341,344,370]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D4BFFB6FFACFEC2FE98FDDBFED6" box="[349,600,345,370]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosus">
<emphasis id="B93BEADAFFB6FFACFEC2FE98FDDBFED6" box="[349,600,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Leptomyrmex pilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to rainforest to the west of Cape Tribulation, 
<collectingRegion id="498BF82AFFB6FFACFA95FE98FA1BFED7" box="[1290,1432,345,371]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Queensland</collectingRegion>
. Morphologically it is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D4BFFB6FFACFDBBFE41FD3CFE3D" box="[548,703,384,409]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aitchisoni">
<emphasis id="B93BEADAFFB6FFACFDBBFE41FD3CFE3D" box="[548,703,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">L. aitchisoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is readily distinguished by the abundant pilosity on all surfaces.
</paragraph>
